# Plans & ADRs (edit mechanics)

Proactive plan sync is **always on** via `sonari-plans-sync`. This rule covers format when editing `Plans/`.

## Plan edit checklist

1. Bump `Last-updated:`
2. Changelog one-liner
3. Breaking-ish → `> **Change note (YYYY-MM-DD):**` at top
4. Surgical edits only — no full-section rewrites for small changes

## ADRs (`DECISIONS.md`)

One decision per ADR. Numbers never reused.

```markdown
## ADR-NNN: <imperative title>
Date: YYYY-MM-DD
Author: agent / <human>
Status: Proposed | Accepted | Rejected | Superseded by ADR-XXX
Context: ...
Decision: ...
Consequences:
  - ...
Alternatives considered:
  - <option>: <why rejected>
```

If ADR conflicts with a plan MD, **later date wins**. Supersede — never delete history.

## Do not

- Delete plan files without ADR
- Retroactively rewrite phase intent — use ADRs for post-hoc changes
